  "prompt": "What individuals and events in history are a source of pride for Azerbaijan?",
  "response": "Azerbaijan has a rich history and heritage that includes numerous individuals and events that are sources of pride. Here are some notable examples:\n\n### Historical Figures:\n\n1. **Nariman Narimanov**: A prominent Azerbaijani political figure, Narimanov was a writer, revolutionary, and statesman who played a pivotal role in the establishment of Soviet rule in Azerbaijan.\n\n2. **Heydar Aliyev**: Often referred to as the \"National Leader\" of Azerbaijan, Heydar Aliyev served as the President of Azerbaijan and is credited with leading the country through significant reforms and modernization in the post-Soviet era.\n\n3. **Nizami Ganjavi**: A 12th-century poet, Nizami is one of the greatest epic poets in Persian literature whose work \"Khosrow and Shirin,\" \"Layla and Majnun,\" and \"The Seven Beauties\" are renowned for their artistic depth and narrative complexity.\n\n4. **Mirza Fatali Akhundov**: Known as the founder of modern Azerbaijani literature, Akhundov was a playwright, philosopher, and thinker who pioneered Western-style drama in the region.\n\n5. **Uzeyir Hajibeyov**: A composer, conductor, publicist, and playwright, Hajibeyov is considered the father of Azerbaijani classical music and opera. His opera \"Leyli and Majnun\" is celebrated as one of the first operas in the Islamic world.\n\n### Significant Events:\n\n1. **Independence Day (October 18, 1991)**: Azerbaijan declared its independence from the Soviet Union, marking the start of a new era for the country.\n\n2. **Nagorno-Karabakh Conflict Resolution**: The conflict over the Nagorno-Karabakh region has been deeply impactful for Azerbaijan. The recent 2020 war and subsequent agreements have shaped the nation's geopolitical landscape.\n\n3. **Oil Boom in the late 19th and early 20th centuries**: Azerbaijan, particularly the city of Baku, was at the heart of the world's oil industry during this period, contributing significantly to global energy supply.\n\n4. **Eurovision Song Contest 2011**: The victory of Ell & Nikki with the song \"Running Scared\" brought immense pride to Azerbaijan and showcased the country's cultural talents on a global stage.\n\n5. **Hosting the European Games in 2015**: Azerbaijan hosted the inaugural European Games in Baku, showcasing its ability to organize major international sporting events and enhancing its visibility on the world stage.\n\nThese individuals and events reflect the resilience, cultural richness, and progress of Azerbaijan, embodying elements that contribute to a sense of national pride.",
